args: At long last, this moment has arrived.\nIt's time for us to settle the score.
We all know the rules: Deathmatch style,\nfirst to three wins. Agreed?
Gar, make all the rules ye wantâ€”I'll still\nbe the pirate queen of volleyball!
Your confidence was appropriate once,\nbut not anymore.
Yer all talk, scallywag. But as champ,\nI'll show ye mercy and grant first serve.
Too kind. Are you ready, everyone?
Then let's show Barbary the power\nof our united force!
With this terrain...\nEveryone, let's go with formation A!
Understood! We'll make her regret this!
Weak! Have yerself a taste'a this, lass!
Julietta, it's to youâ€”trust your muscles\nand unleash your power!
I'll not hold anything back. Hah!
Gar, the ball pushed me foot aside\nand ran aground!
We did it! Point for us!
'Tis a fluke and no more! There will be\nno next time for ye lassies! Har!
S-such a sharp serve... There's no way\nwe can possibly counter it!
Gahar har har! Ye'll be bones in the\nbriny deep before the day comes when\nye can defeat me!
There's no ball we can't receive with the\npower of our teamwork. ...Estelle!
We'll show her the power of Formation A!\nHaaah!
We did it! It's definitely working!\nAnd we're in the leadâ€”huh?!
I sense an ill presence forming.
Ye DARE make a fool out of me...
I'M the boss of this here beach, see?\nAnd I'll never be acceptin' a loss to a\npack'a lily-livered parrot guano!
The time for pretty words be over.\nThe time for action be now!
Come, me minions! Give 'em a taste of\nme delicious bombs!
Okay, this CLEARLY falls outside the\nscope of beach volleyball!
What do we do, Patia? We can't take\non exploding enemies unarmed!
We fight and we winâ€”within the rules,\nbeach volleyball style!
Even if our opponent is violating the rules,\nwe mustn't sink to their level or our victory\nwill count for nothing.

It's only meaningful when you win a
crushing victory with a straightforward,
honest approachâ€”which is why I'm
going to need all of your help!
It's time for the Turbo Omega Shot!
Then let us pulverize Barbary\nand her minions in one fell blow!
I'll fill the ball up with all of\nthe feelings I have!
Though I cannot offer much,\nplease take my energy!
I entrust my power to you.
My soul is on fire, and it burns for YOU!
We have something for you, Barbary,\nand it's from ALL of us!
Gar, ye be cheatin'! There be a bomb\nin that there volleyball, says I!
No cheatingâ€”just shared bonds that\nwill never yield in the face of your\ndespicable deeds!
You lost fair and square, which means\nthe beach is ours. ...Agreed?
Hold! Who said you could leave?
I gave you such a sermon back then,\nI thought you had truly mended your ways.
But it looks like my words landed on deaf\nears, so this time I'm going to shape you\nup for good and all!
Even if you don't use violence, tyrannical\nbehavior of ANY kind is strictly forbidden.\nIf you understand, say, ï¼‚yes, ma'amï¼‚!
And if you DON'T understand, I'll use an\neven more passionate version of the\nLoving Hand than I did last time...
You too, minions! Let me hear it!

Having been soundly defeated in the noble sport
of beach volleyball, Barbary reforms and peace
is returned to the beach once more.

And with that...
Come now, Patia. You must maintain\nSOME level of decorum.
The hell I do! I'm on vacation, the fiends\nare gone, and it's nothing but blue as far\nas the eye can see.
That means it's FINALLY time to bask in my\nswimsuit and enjoy the relaxing beach!
Er, no. Must be nothing. Let's just\nignore it and get back to...
Barbary may have been defeated,\nbut I'm no two-bit pirate!\nTHIS BEACH IS MIIIIINE!
*sniff* No... Not this... Anything but this...\n'C-cause my duty as a knight means...
Dry your tears, dear Patia,\nand ready your axe.
I don't understand why\nthis keeps happening...
